Interface OrderService

All Known Implementing Classes:
OrderServiceImpl
public interface OrderService
OrderService is an interface that defines the methods for managing order-related operations. These methods include creating, retrieving, updating orders, and querying orders by various criteria like status or user ID.

The methods in this interface throw BadRequestException, NotFoundException, and DataMappingException when the input is invalid, or when the requested order data is not found.
